				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have like nobody to talk to about these sorts of things, so I decided maybe I could get some feedback from fellow brellians who might have some knowledge to share. This post is not for sympathy nor pity. I just need help.
<br />

<br />
Here's the situation:
<br />

<br />
Ok my girlfriend is under 18. She's 16 going on 17. She lives in a household of 5. Theres her, her mother, her sister, her brother, and a guy who rents one of the rooms. Her sister and brother are of young age. The mother works barely over minimum wage and is getting kicked out of her house (as well as the kids) due to a really dumb situation. She claims that she can't afford even low-income housing. (like the little 2 room apartment thingys)
<br />

<br />
The mother had just informed me that they are considering actually putting themselves in a homeless shelter, as they have no other place to go. Well, they do, but the mother would rather live in a homeless shelter, and drag her kids along with her then to temporarily live with nearby family members she doesn't get along with. Pretty messed up, eh? 
<br />

<br />
I coulden't think of a realistic way of helping my girlfriend in this situation. Her mother has legal control over her and she is getting dragged into the shelter with her. Theres not much I can do. I don't have any money to give to help them. I don't have a place for them to stay, given that the cold hearted nature of my family would naturally rule out that option.
<br />

<br />
The only thing I've come up with is to go with her to the shelter, leave my happy little computer-chair for awhile and tough it out with the homeless folk until they can get a place. I won't be seperated from her. I don't want her to have to face a life like that alone... it's very clear that her mother doesn't love her. Her mom has made very bad decisions in her life which have led her to this inevitablility. She blames it all on her daughter. Everything and anything. Well, back to the subject.
<br />

<br />
Anybody have legal advice? Could my girlfriend get emancipated? I seriously don't know what to do in this situation, I greatly appreciate any feedback that I can get.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.bobsagetisgod.com/sagetbox.gif" border="0" />
<br />
Omgosh r0x0r ^^</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
