				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Emancipation usually requires:
<br />
1) Steady, well-paying job
<br />
2) Proof of housing
<br />
3) Proof of stability
<br />

<br />
If memory serves correct there are a number of programs that would allow a mother of three to live in section 8 housing at minimal (or no) cost to them.  Prior to getting the boot, she should look into the welfare (both government and non-government) groups.
<br />

<br />
Not knowing what your living situation is, it's harder to know what advice to give.  Having a mother that taught in high-risk areas for 20+ years, I've seen lots of creative 'it takes a village' situations.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
