				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If your girlfriend is pushed into a job at 16 to help pay, it's likely that she will end up dropping out of high school and working full time.  That's a recipe for never getting out of that situatiion.
<br />

<br />
I would just be careful about your girlfriend sharing too much responsibility to pay bills at a young age.  Gotta do what you must to survive, but consider where she will be 3 years from now too.
<br />

<br />
I agree that there should be some kind of assistance available.  It also seems that if the mother doesn't want to live with relatives, how about just the kids?  Is that an optiion?
<br />

<br />
Does the mother own a car?  I know a single mom that pays for rent with a paper route.  I delievered pizza for a while once myself and the tips can be pretty good.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
